        "title": "refactor(whatsapp): add inbound admission foundation",
        "body": "## Summary\n\n- add optional `WebInboundMessage.admission` for accepted WhatsApp inbound messages\n- build admission in inbound access-control and attach it during monitor message construction\n- preserve PR #88245 live flat alias compatibility and leave downstream consumers on existing fields\n\n## Scope\n\nThis is the admission foundation only. It does not migrate identity/peer resolution, reply delivery, agent context/dispatch, or post-admission lifecycle handoff cleanup.\n\n## Verification\n\n- `pnpm tsgo:extensions`\n- `node scripts/run-vitest.mjs extensions/whatsapp/src/inbound/access-control.test.ts extensions/whatsapp/src/inbound/message-aliases.test.ts extensions/whatsapp/src/monitor-inbox.behavior.test.ts`\n- `git diff --check origin/main..HEAD`\n\n## Notes\n\n- Accepted access-control results include admission.\n- Blocked access-control results do not expose admission.\n- Monitor-created messages attach admission through `withDeprecatedWebInboundMessageFlatAliases(...)`.\n- Existing flat `WebInboundMessage` fields remain live getter/setter aliases.\n- Blacksmith Testbox-through-Crabbox was attempted, but remote DNS failed before command execution; no remote pass is claimed.\n",
